                    "body": "Ah, that makes sense as an explanation for the docs, thanks.\r\n\r\nBut the following still fails, and having a decoding error option would be useful in general, no?\r\n{code:java}\r\ncsv = \"\"\"\r\ncol_1,col2\r\n0,\ud83d\ude00\r\n1,b\r\n\"\"\".encode(\"utf-8\")\r\n\r\npa.csv.read_csv(io.BytesIO(csv), pa.csv.ReadOptions(encoding=\"ascii\")){code}\r\n{noformat}\r\n>>> UnicodeDecodeError: 'ascii' codec can't decode byte 0xf0 in position 14: ordinal not in range(128)\r\n{noformat}",
